# Menu Configuration Documentation

<Tabs>
    <TabItem value="filters" label="filters.yml">

        ## Filters Menu Configuration

        ### Menu Title
        ```yaml
        title:
          user: "&b&lFilter Menu - Page (&a&l%currentPage%&b&l) &7(&c%type%&7)"
          global: "&b&lGlobal Filter Menu - Page (&a&l%currentPage%&b&l) &7(&c%type%&7)"
        ```
        - Dynamic placeholders:
        - `%currentPage%`: Shows current page number
        - `%type%`: Displays filter type

        ### Navigation Items
        | Slot | Item          | Action           | Description                                                                 |
        |------|---------------|------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------|
        | 0    | Information   | NOTHING          | Explains filter management mechanics                                        |
        | 1    | Back          | PREVIOUS_PAGE    | Returns to previous page (Arrow-left skull)                                 |
        | 4    | Close         | CLOSE            | Closes menu (Red X skull)                                                   |
        | 8    | Next          | NEXT_PAGE        | Advances to next page (Arrow-right skull)                                   |

        **Information Lore Details:**
        ```yaml
        - "&7To add items, simply click and drag them into your inventory."
        - "&7Swift right-click to add with 'ignore amount' and 'ignore metadata' enabled."
        - "&7Shift left-click to add with 'ignore amount' and 'ignore metadata' disabled."
        - "&7Right-click to add with 'ignore amount' enabled and 'ignore metadata' disabled."
        - "&7Left-click to add with 'ignore amount' disabled and 'ignore metadata' enabled."
        - "&7To remove an item from filters, just click on it."
        ```
        > ðŸ’¡ Pro Tip: Different click types enable various filter modes

